Italy beat England 4-2 on penalties
following a 0-0 tie to set up a European Championship soccer
semifinal against record three-time champion Germany.  Alessandro Diamanti scored the winning kick in the shootout
after  Ashley Cole â€™s penalty had been saved by  Gianluigi Buffon 
at the Olympic Stadium in Kiev, Ukraine. Ashley Young also
failed to score for England, while Riccardo Montolivo hit his
kick wide.  Italy had 35 shots to nine for England during the 120
minutes of play and 64 percent possession. It will play Germany
on June 28 in Warsaw, Poland. The other semifinal will be
between defending champion Spain and Portugal the previous day.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
